cs.SY, cs.ET, cs.CE, cs.PF, cs.EM

Reasoning: The paper discusses the modeling and control of microgrids, which involves the application of systems and control theory to electrical power systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the basic notions and definitions in power systems, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.ET (Electricity and Magnetism). Additionally, the paper discusses the components and functionality of microgrids, which could fall under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) or cs.PF (Physics and Society). Finally, the paper presents detailed dynamical models of microgrid components, which could also fall under cs.EM (Electromagnetics).
